(SHA3-384, HPK, and Addressing) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Date: 2026-04-10) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document explains how Atho uses SHA3-384 across identity, transaction digesting, block) Tj
T*
(identity, and runtime integrity checks. It focuses on the active implementation profile, not) Tj
T*
(historical variants.) Tj
T*
(- Hash Primitive Role in Atho) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho uses SHA3-384 as the default high-assurance digest primitive for consensus-relevant) Tj
T*
(identity and signing flows. The practical result is a consistent 48-byte digest shape \(96 hex) Tj
T*
(characters\) across major subsystems.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Core implementation entrypoints:) Tj
T*
(- Src/Utility/hash.py) Tj
T*
(- Src/Utility/txdhash.py) Tj
T*
(- Src/Transactions/tx.py) Tj
T*
(- Src/Transactions/txvalidation.py) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SHA3-256 remains present for specific helper/checksum use cases where shorter digest width is) Tj
T*
(sufficient and consensus behavior is unaffected.) Tj
T*
(- HPK \(Hashed Public Key\) Model) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(HPK is derived from raw Falcon public key bytes through SHA3-384. This gives deterministic,) Tj
T*
(fixed-length identity material for internal destination binding.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key properties:) Tj
T*
(- digest size: 48 bytes,) Tj
T*
(- hex form: 96 chars,) Tj
T*
(- deterministic for identical input bytes,) Tj
T*
(- stable across display encoding changes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters:) Tj
T*
(- internal storage and validation remain hash-native,) Tj
T*
(- user-facing address encodings can evolve without changing canonical identity semantics,) Tj
T*
(- code paths that operate on HPK avoid variable-length public key edge cases.) Tj
T*
(- Public Key Length Policy) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Current production constants in Src/Utility/const.py define:) Tj
T*
(- canonical Falcon public key length 897 bytes,) Tj
T*
(- optional legacy compatibility length 1024 bytes \(disabled in normal operation unless migration) Tj
T*
(policy enables it\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(HPK derivation always hashes the raw byte payload accepted by validation policy. Display) Tj
T*
(encoding is not part of HPK digest input.) Tj
T*
(- Addressing Layer: HPK vs Base56) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho separates internal and external address representations:) Tj
T*
(- internal: HPK-based deterministic identity,) Tj
T*
(- external: Base56 user-facing strings with network and role-aware prefixes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
