T*
() Tj
T*
(Digest security is not only about algorithm selection; context separation is equally important.) Tj
T*
(Atho uses role and network domain tags in several derivation paths to prevent cross-context) Tj
T*
(replay and address-role confusion.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Examples include:) Tj
T*
(- regular/bond/stake address role domains,) Tj
T*
(- network-specific pool address derivation domains,) Tj
T*
(- private-layer domain-tagged commitment/signature contexts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Best practice when adding new hash usages:) Tj
T*
(- define explicit domain labels,) Tj
T*
(- avoid reusing digest outputs across unrelated contexts,) Tj
T*
(- keep input serialization deterministic,) Tj
T*
(- include network or role tags when replay boundaries are required.) Tj
